  - type: features
    section_theme: bg-body-tertiary text-body
    title: Areas of Focus
    card_list:
      - name: Anxiety & Depression
        desc: Finding relief from persistent worry, low mood, and the patterns that keep you feeling stuck.
        expanded_desc: Persistent worry, low mood, and a sense of being stuck can make everyday life feel overwhelming. We work with you to identify the patterns driving these feelings, develop practical coping strategies, and rediscover a sense of calm, purpose, and possibility.
      - name: Mood & Behavior disorders
        desc: Support for managing emotional regulation, impulsivity, and the challenges of daily functioning.
        expanded_desc: Managing intense emotions and impulsive behaviors can feel exhausting — for you and the people around you. We offer structured, evidence-based support to help you regulate your emotions, understand your patterns, and build a more stable and fulfilling daily life.
      - name: Emotional Overwhelm/ Life Transitions
        desc: Navigating change, loss, and the moments when life feels like too much to carry alone.
        expanded_desc: Major life changes — a new job, a loss, a move, a relationship shift — can leave you feeling unmoored. We help you process the emotions that come with change, find your footing again, and move forward with clarity and confidence.
      - name: Self-harm / Suicidal Thoughts
        desc: A safe, non‑judgmental space to address pain, find stability, and build reasons for hope, with support that meets you exactly where you are.
        expanded_desc: If you're struggling with thoughts of self-harm or suicide, you don't have to face them alone. We provide a compassionate, non-judgmental space where you can speak openly, find stability, and work together toward hope and healing.
      - name: Behavioral Issues
        desc: Addressing patterns of behavior that affect relationships, work, and overall quality of life.
        expanded_desc: Patterns of behavior that affect your relationships, work, or daily functioning don't have to define you. We work collaboratively to understand what's driving these patterns and develop practical strategies for lasting, meaningful change.
      - name: Faith & Spiritual Struggles
        desc: Integrating Christian faith and values into the healing process in a way that feels authentic to you.
        expanded_desc: For those who desire it, faith can be a powerful part of the healing process. We offer Christian counseling that honors your beliefs and integrates your values into therapy — helping you find spiritual grounding alongside emotional and psychological growth.
      - name: Parenting Struggles
        desc: Support for the stress, uncertainty, and adjustment that comes with raising children at any stage.
        expanded_desc: Parenting is one of the most rewarding and demanding roles there is. Whether you're navigating a difficult stage, managing behavioral challenges, or simply feeling overwhelmed, we offer compassionate support to help you show up for your children and yourself.
      - name: Trauma & Attachment
        desc: Healing from past wounds and  building secure, trusting relationships at every stage of life
        expanded_desc: Trauma can shape the way we see ourselves and connect with others. Whether you've experienced a single difficult event or a lifetime of painful relationships, we provide a safe, supportive space to process what happened, rebuild trust, and develop more secure ways of relating to the people in your life.
